# Phase 0 — Orchestrator pre-flight checklist

Tick each box BEFORE spawning any sub-agent.

## Context loaded

- [ ] `CLAUDE.md` (project root) read end-to-end.
- [ ] Every per-package `CLAUDE.md` (`apps/*/CLAUDE.md`, `packages/*/CLAUDE.md`) read.
- [ ] `~/.claude/projects/<slug>/memory/MEMORY.md` read; each pointed-to file read.
- [ ] Prior `*-READINESS.md`, `*-REPORT.md`, `MORNING-REPORT.md` (if any) read.
- [ ] Project-specific orchestrator doc (`ORCHESTRATOR.md`, `AGENTS.md`) read.

## Baselines run

- [ ] Toolchain check (`scripts/verify-env.sh` or equivalent).
- [ ] Typecheck across all workspaces.
- [ ] Lint across all workspaces.
- [ ] Unit / integration tests (pass-rate captured).
- [ ] E2E happy-path (pass-rate captured).
- [ ] Each result written into `.orchestrator/state.md` under "Baselines".

## Queue initialised

- [ ] `bash ~/.claude/skills/orchestrator-protocol/scripts/orchctl-init.sh` run.
- [ ] `.orchestrator/tasks/{inbox,in-progress,done,escalated}` exist.
- [ ] `.orchestrator/state.md` exists with Baselines, Producer ledger, Consumer ledger sections.
- [ ] `.orchestrator/` is in `.gitignore` on `main`.
- [ ] `.gitattributes` on `main` has `merge=union` for append-only docs.
- [ ] Both above committed as `chore(orch): prepare orchestrator infra` (or confirmed already present).

## Plan doc written

- [ ] `docs/<mission>-plan-<DATE>.md` exists at repo root or under docs/.
- [ ] Workstreams enumerated with: id, wave, branch name, sub-agent type, depends-on, must-read.
- [ ] Workstream list either authored manually OR generated via `/goal` invocation.

## Optional goal-planning step

- [ ] `/goal` (or `goal-planner` sub-agent) invoked if the mission is open-ended.
- [ ] Decomposition output saved to `docs/<mission>-goal-plan.md`.
- [ ] Decomposition reviewed for sane workstream boundaries before Wave 1 spawns.

## Spawn-readiness

- [ ] All Wave 1 sub-agent briefs drafted from `templates/subagent-prompt.md.tmpl`.
- [ ] Each brief has its agent profile applied (see `agent-profiles/<archetype>.yaml`).
- [ ] Every brief includes the verbatim hard-rules block.
- [ ] Every brief has a single observable Done-when criterion.
- [ ] Every brief specifies `isolation: worktree` and `run_in_background: true`.

If every box above is ticked, you can spawn Wave 1 in a single multi-Agent message.
